==== Epigenetic Age Acceleration

Poor sleep is associated with cellular and epigenetic aging:

- *Telomere shortening*: Short sleep duration, sleep apnea, and insomnia are significantly associated with shorter telomeres (biological marker of cellular aging) @Mazzotti2023SleepQualityTelomere
- *Epigenetic clocks*: Sleep traits have causal effects on epigenetic age acceleration via Mendelian randomization analysis @SleepTraits2024EpigeneticAgeAcceleration
- *Insomnia and aging*: Insomnia symptoms are significantly associated with epigenetic age acceleration markers in >2,000 women @Carroll2017InsomniaEpigeneticAging

Immune cells are particularly affected: sleep deprivation alters innate and adaptive immune parameters, leading to chronic inflammation and telomere attrition in immune cells @Besedovsky2021SleepDeprivationImmune.

